  <h2>Markets Worth Knowing</h2>

  <p>
    Pasar Santa in Kebayoran Baru is a three-floor market that rewards an afternoon visit. The lower floors operate as a traditional market from early morning. The upper floor, where independent vendors sell vintage clothing, thrift finds, accessories, and street food, comes alive after 2 PM and is most active from 6 PM onward. Most stalls on the upper floor are closed on Mondays. The address is Jalan Cipaku I, Petogogan, roughly 10 minutes from Kemang by car.
  </p>

  <p>
    Brightspot Market is a quarterly pop-up that has run for over 15 years, bringing together independent design labels, food vendors, and live music. It typically appears at Agora Mall in Thamrin across several weekend days. The schedule is published through the Brightspot app and their social channels. Sunday Market SCBD operates in the SCBD area with a focus on natural and locally sourced goods. Both events are intermittent, so checking dates before travelling is necessary.
  </p>

